Main Element


The element <main> is used to encapsulate the dominant 
content within a webpage. This tag is separate from the 
<footer> and the <nav> of a web page since these elements 
donâ€™t contain the principal content.

<main>
  <header>
    <h1>Types of Sports</h1>
  </header>
  <article>
    <h3>Baseball</h3>
    <p>
      The first game of baseball was played in Cooperstown, New York in the summer of 1839.
    </p>
  </article>
</main>

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////


Footer Element


The footer contains information such as:

Contact information
Copyright information
Terms of use
Site Map
Reference to top of page links

<footer>
  <p>Email me at Codey@Codecademy.com</p>
</footer